---
const title = 'Clowns and Mimes, on Miscellaneous Topological Spaces... IN THE DARK';
---
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta name="color-scheme" content="dark light" />
    <title>{title}</title>
    <meta name="description" content="A team tag game played on labyrinths that wrap in unusual ways." />
    <link rel="icon" href="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg' viewBox='0 0 16 16'%3E%3Ccircle cx='8' cy='8' r='7' fill='%23111'/%3E%3C/svg%3E" />
    <style>
      :root { color-scheme: dark; }
      body { margin: 0; font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; background: #0c0c0e; color: #eee; }
      main { max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 4rem 1.25rem; }
      h1 { font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 4vw, 2.4rem); line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
      h2 { margin-top: 2.5rem; }
      a { color: #cfd; }
      .lede { color: #bbb; font-size: 1.1rem; }
      .download-buttons { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.75rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
      .download-buttons a { background: #1a1a1d; padding: 0.7rem 1.1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; text-decoration: none; border: 1px solid #2a2a2e; }
      footer { color: #777; margin-top: 4rem; font-size: 0.9rem; }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main>
      <h1>{title}</h1>
      <p class="lede">A team tag game played on a dimly lit labyrinth that wraps in unusual ways.</p>

      <h2>Download</h2>
      <div class="download-buttons">
        <a id="dl-windows" href="https://github.com/sean-reid/clowns-and-mimes/releases/latest">Windows</a>
        <a id="dl-macos" href="https://github.com/sean-reid/clowns-and-mimes/releases/latest">macOS</a>
        <a id="dl-linux" href="https://github.com/sean-reid/clowns-and-mimes/releases/latest">Linux</a>
      </div>

      <h2>How to play</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Pick host, code, or strangers.</li>
        <li>Everyone spawns in the center. Sixty seconds to move freely.</li>
        <li>Turns alternate between the mime team and the clown team. Tag opponents during your turn to freeze them.</li>
        <li>Win by freezing every opponent. Lose if your team is all frozen.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Topologies</h2>
      <p>The arena is a finite plane, a torus, a Klein bottle, or a sphere. The host picks in private games. Random in open lobbies.</p>

      <h2>Source</h2>
      <p><a href="https://github.com/sean-reid/clowns-and-mimes">GitHub</a></p>

      <footer>MIT licensed. Built by Sean Reid.</footer>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
